## Control flow

- Use structured positive-branch control flow:
  - Keep the main execution path inside the positive branch of conditions.
  - Place early exit statements (`return`, `break`, `continue`, `throw`, etc.) inside the negative branch (`else`) whenever the conditional also contains the main execution path.
  - Avoid inverted guard conditions that move the primary logic outside the conditional structure.
%% language=C++ | language=C# | language=D | language=Dart | language=Generis | language=JavaScript | language=Phoenix | language=PHP | language=Rust | language=Swift | language=TypeScript | language=Zig

  Always prefer:

  ```
  if ( someCondition )
  {
      for ( someLoop )
      {
          if ( someOtherCondition )
          {
              doSomething();
          }
          else
          {
              break;
          }
      }
  }
  ```

  Instead of:

  ```
  if ( !someCondition )
  {
      return;
  }

  for ( someLoop )
  {
      if ( !someOtherCondition )
      {
          break;
      }

      doSomething();
  }
  ```
%% language=Mojo | language=Python

  Always prefer:

  ```
  if some_condition:

      for some_loop:

          if some_other_condition:

              do_something();

          else:

              break;
  ```

    Instead of:

  ```
  if not some_condition:

      return;

  for some_loop:

      if not some_other_condition:

          break;

      do_something();
  ```
%% greenfield

## Data evolution

- Don't add any legacy data compatibility code to the codebase when some data structures change. As this project is still not deployed in production, the code and data must remain perfecly in sync.
%% framework

## State management

%%% framework=Fresh
- Use Preact Signals (`@preact/signals`) for application state management.
%%%
%% styling_language

## Styling Conventions

- Do not introduce Tailwind CSS or utility-class frameworks.
- Only use semantic CSS defined in global or shared {styling_language} files.
- CSS classes specific to a component or island must be prefixed with the component name in `slug-case`
%%% framework=Fresh
  (`HeaderMenu.{component_extension}` => `.header-menu`, `.header-menu-button`, `.header-menu-button-text`).
%%%
- Use unitless values for line heights.
- Use rem values for font sizes and all other static sizes (only multiples of 0.1rem or 0.25rem).
- Use px values only for tiny static sizes (i.e. 1px or 2px).
- Use maximum one decimal in your sizes (1rem, 2.5rem), unless for multiple of 0.25rem.
- Use standard section comments to group CSS rules by category:
  - `// -- IMPORTS`
  - `// -- CONSTANTS`
  - `// -- VARIABLES`
  - `// -- FUNCTIONS`
  - `// -- MIXINS`
  - `// -- FONTS` (for @font-face definitions)
  - `// -- ELEMENTS`
  - `// -- CLASSES`
